description:
Create src/components/tick-column.ts:

@customElement('tick-column')
export class TickColumn extends LitElement {
  @property() name!: string;  // blocked, ready, in-progress, review, done
  @property() color!: string; // Column header color
  @property({ type: Array }) ticks: Tick[] = [];
}

Features:
- Column header with name and tick count
- Color-coded header bar matching existing UI:
  - blocked: red (#f38ba8)
  - ready: yellow (#f9e2af)
  - in-progress: blue (#89b4fa)
  - review: mauve (#cba6f7)
  - done: green (#a6e3a1)
- Scrollable content area with tick-card children
- Empty state message when no ticks

Test: Render column with 3 mock ticks, verify header, count, and cards render
